{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":22820,"name":"Konstantin Guschin","username":"kostik1337","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/{size}/123_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T07:26:53.702Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello everybody, I am trying to load and display simple orthogonal timlemap, the problem is there are seams between same tiles. Picture below illustrates the problem\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/5/52e8367339072515e305e64dab4f817a40dc69f6.png\" alt=\"Selection_006\" width=\"665\" height=\"500\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd here is minimalistic sample\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/br391ke4pabrimq/test.zip?dl=0\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/br391ke4pabrimq/test.zip?dl=0\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAs you can see in sample, those seams desappear and appear again, when you move camera (with wsad). It looks like texture coordinates are moving a bit when you moving camera.\u003cbr\u003e\nSo, I’d like to know, why does this happen and how can I avoid it? One obvious solution is to add 1px border to each tile with the same color as tile, but this looks like hack, and probably won’t fix the problem fundamentally.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T07:26:53.702Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":17,"reads":48,"readers_count":47,"score":94.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Konstantin Guschin","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.dropbox.com/s/br391ke4pabrimq/test.zip?dl=0","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Dropbox - test.zip","clicks":5}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":638,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22822,"name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T10:50:12.103Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis doesn’t work? \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"onebox whitelistedgeneric\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003cimg src=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/images/default-favicon.ico\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/sprite-texture-nearest-neighbour-filtering/3422/4?u=modanung\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eUrho3D\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003cimg src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/200/123_1.png\" class=\"thumbnail onebox-avatar\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\"\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/sprite-texture-nearest-neighbour-filtering/3422/4?u=modanung\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eSprite/Texture Nearest Neighbour Filtering\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWell, this already has an answer, but I’d like to add - I fixed the same problem with  engineParameters_[\"TextureFilterMode\"] = FILTER_NEAREST;  at Setup() of your Application, this sets filtering type for all textures, if they don’t have an xml file\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’d look at the map and tiles, but I’m not creating a Google account to download a file.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T10:51:05.867Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":28.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/sprite-texture-nearest-neighbour-filtering/3422/4","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Sprite/Texture Nearest Neighbour Filtering","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22823,"name":"Konstantin Guschin","username":"kostik1337","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/{size}/123_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T11:03:39.206Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"3931\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/40/1123_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Modanung:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis doesn’t work? \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnfortunately, no, this makes no effect. I tried setting different filtering and address modes, they don’t seem to effect too.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"3931\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/40/1123_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Modanung:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’d look at the map and tiles, but I’m not creating a Google account to download a file.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHuh? Dropbox doesn’t require you to have google account, just press “No thanks” button at the bottom.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T11:03:39.206Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":24.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Konstantin Guschin","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Modanung","name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":638,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22825,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T11:18:36.174Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf sprite vertices are aligned and texture is good, there shan’t be any seams between. I saw similar problems in sample games, will investigate it later.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T11:18:36.174Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":41,"readers_count":40,"score":13.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22827,"name":"Konstantin Guschin","username":"kostik1337","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/{size}/123_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T11:29:40.779Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks. Also, i forgot to mention - if camera zoom is integer, those seams seem to be constant, moving camera does not affect them.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T11:29:40.779Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":8.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Konstantin Guschin","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":638,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22846,"name":"Konstantin Guschin","username":"kostik1337","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/{size}/123_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T15:27:15.304Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI’ve done some research, and first off, Modanung was right. Changing filtering to nearest really fixed the problem on that map. My apologies, I should’ve tested it before.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut I’ve got similar problem on another map, and here it does not helps. More correct, it helps a bit, those seams appear quite rarely, but they are. This is what it looks like:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/9b2de1a7eee96eeb2794ac24fbd04a75e09e5ecb.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"640\" height=\"500\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, I’ve updated dropbox archive with new map.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI tried to place sprites on the scene by hand without TileMap, like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eNode@ spritesNode = scene_.CreateChild();\nTexture2D@ texture = cache.GetResource(\"Texture2D\", \"grass9.png\");\nSprite2D@ sprite = Sprite2D();\nsprite.texture = texture;\nsprite.rectangle = IntRect(32, 32, 64, 64);\nSprite2D@ sprite2 = Sprite2D();\nsprite2.texture = texture;\nsprite2.rectangle = IntRect(128, 32, 160, 64);\n\nfor (int r = 0; r\u0026lt; 50; ++r) {\n    for (int i = 0; i\u0026lt; 50; ++i) {\n        Node@ spriteNode = spritesNode.CreateChild(\"StaticSprite2D\");\n        spriteNode.position2D = Vector2(i * 32 * PIXEL_SIZE, r * 32 * PIXEL_SIZE);\n\n        StaticSprite2D@ staticSprite = spriteNode.CreateComponent(\"StaticSprite2D\");\n        staticSprite.sprite = (r+i)%6 \u0026lt; 3 ? sprite : sprite2;\n    }\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand problem stayed, so I believe, vertices are aligned and texture is OK.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there anything I should try?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T15:27:15.304Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":38,"readers_count":37,"score":12.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Konstantin Guschin","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":638,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22848,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T15:32:18.596Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"3931\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/40/123_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e kostik1337:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMore correct, it helps a bit, those seams appear quite rarely, but they are. This is what it looks like:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThis\u003c/em\u003e looks like bad texture. You just have dirty brown tile data.\u003cbr\u003e\nAre these seams 100% visible?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T15:32:18.596Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":12.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22849,"name":"Konstantin Guschin","username":"kostik1337","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/kostik1337/{size}/123_2.png","created_at":"2018-01-10T15:37:57.417Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eCan you elaborate, please? What do you mean at bad texture - a broken texture?\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd what do you mean at 100% visible, you mean they are not transparent?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-01-10T15:37:57.417Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":12.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3931,"topic_slug":"seams-on-tilemaps","display_username":"Konstantin Guschin","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"ca